The Kenya Meteorological Department on Wednesday said most counties will be sunny tomorrow. The Met said the temperatures will range from 11 degrees to 25 degrees. It said in the early morning, Narok and Nyeri will have 11 degrees while the coastal counties will have 25 degrees.Lodwar and Marsabit are expected to be sunny and windy In the late afternoon Lodwar, Garissa and Turkana will have the highest temperatures at 38, 37 and 37 degrees, respectively. Nairobi will be at 28 degrees while Nyeri will have the lowest at 25 degrees, according to the chart shared by the Met. In June last year, the weatherman warned that other parts that will be affected by the winds include Northwestern, Northeastern and Eastern. In an advisory, the forecaster warned of damages Lamu, Kilifi, Mombasa, Kwale and Tana River, Kitui, Garissa, Isiolo, Wajir, Marsabit, Samburu, Turkana and Mandera. Read more on:Met warns of strong, dangerous winds along Coastal region Click here for the latest political news